Program: Outlook
Title: Doris Appiah: Bipolar and kept in chains
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yz0ct
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 16 Oct 2012
Lucy Ash speaks to Doris Appiah, the Ghanaian woman who suffered abuse for years at a prayer camp which claimed it could cure her mental illness. Also, from the UK, we hear from Sandra O'Connor who has 'faceblindness'- and very few friends as a result, and Sipho "Hotstix" Mabuse, the legendary South African drummer, who went back to school 40 years after he dropped out Show less